NET

INCOME DURING THE FOURTH AND THIRD QUARTERS OF 2003 INCLUDED AFTER-TAX NET GAINS RELATED TO NON-CURRENT INVESTMENTS OF $5 MILLION AND $1 MILLION,

RESPECTIVELY. NET INCOME FOR THE FOURTH QUARTER ALSO INCLUDED SETTLEMENT OF THE COMPANY'S FORWARD PURCHASE AGREEMENT RESULTING IN A GAIN OF $6 MILLION AND A FAVORABLE CUMULATIVE-EFFECT TYPE

ADJUSTMENT RELATED TO THE ADOPTION OF SFAS 150 OF $3 MILLION. NET INCOME (LOSS)

100

DURING

